					<description><![CDATA[<p>Accountancy is becoming an increasingly competitive profession, and employers have high demands for accountants they hire to audit their revenue. It is important to stand out to get the best opportunities, and certain characteristics will help you achieve this with the best accountant. This article contains a comprehensive and detailed discussion about some qualities a good accountant should possess. Whether you own a business enterprise or are an aspiring accountant yourself, this article will shed light on all that it takes to excel in this field. 1. Sharp Analytical Skills Being able to think analytically is a crucial skill needed to be a great accountant. You need to be able to interpret and assess large pieces of financial data and ... <a title="Top 7 Characteristics of a Great Accountant" class="read-more" href="https://moneyqanda.com/characteristics-great-accountant/" aria-label="Read more about Top 7 Characteristics of a Great Accountant">Read more</a></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://moneyqanda.com/characteristics-great-accountant/">Top 7 Characteristics of a Great Accountant</a> appeared first on <a href="https://moneyqanda.com">Money Q&amp;A</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="560" height="315" src="https://moneyqanda.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/when-should-you-hire-an-accountant.png" alt="When Should You Hire an Accountant" class="wp-image-16909" srcset="https://moneyqanda.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/when-should-you-hire-an-accountant.png 560w, https://moneyqanda.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/when-should-you-hire-an-accountant-300x169.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px" /></figure>



<p>Accountancy is becoming an increasingly competitive profession, and employers have high demands for accountants they hire to audit their revenue. It is important to stand out to get the best opportunities, and certain characteristics will help you achieve this with the best accountant. </p>



<p>This article contains a comprehensive and detailed discussion about some qualities a good accountant should possess. Whether you own a business enterprise or are an aspiring accountant yourself, this article will shed light on all that it takes to excel in this field.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-1-sharp-analytical-skills">1. Sharp Analytical Skills</h2>



<p>Being able to think analytically is a crucial skill needed to be a great accountant. You need to be able to interpret and assess large pieces of financial data and draw relevant conclusions. Analyzing financial reports correctly, identifying trends, and giving meaningful comments based on the analysis are some examples of good analytical skills.</p>



<p>Moreover, good accountants know how to guide their clients or the organizations they work for by pinpointing potential risks and opportunities and giving recommendations on how to avoid or capitalize on them. </p>



<p>Concisely presenting your data analysis requires some technical skills like know-how of accounting software as well as the necessary communication skills to convey highly complicated financial pieces of advice to stakeholders with no experience in the field.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-2-willingness-to-learn">2. Willingness to Learn</h2>



<p>It is crucial to keep your sources of knowledge broad when pursuing a degree in accounting. Take in as much input as you can regarding your field and synthesize it in a way that benefits you most. It is also important to learn in a way that’s most convenient to your circumstances. </p>



<p>For example, you can pursue an <a href="https://online.peru.edu/undergraduate-programs/business-administration-accounting/">online bachelor of business administration accounting</a> if you do not have the means and conveyance for physical classes. An online course can also be undertaken by accountants seeking further education in their field.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-3-client-centric">3. Client-Centric</h2>



<p>According to research, around <a href="https://onpay.com/hr/basics/2019-small-business-finance-hr">70% of small businesses</a> don’t have an accountant. While a good accountant should be able to provide strong input, it is important to fulfill your client’s needs and expectations. </p>



<p>Your primary goal should be to meet the requirements presented by the client based on their business niche. A thorough understanding of the industry, coupled with a good work ethic, will help you make financial decisions that will satisfy your client.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-4-good-communication-skills">4. Good Communication Skills</h2>



<p>We can’t sufficiently stress how important it is to be a proficient communicator. Being an accountant, you will meet a multitude of different people belonging to different industries every day. Excellent communication is necessary because it is required to build your client’s trust and develop a long-lasting relationship with them. </p>



<p>Furthermore, you will often find yourself advising people with minimal knowledge of finance and accounting. It is vital to get your message across in understandable terms to ensure everyone is on the same page.</p>



<p>Strong communication skills are also needed to understand your client well. In turn, you can ensure you help them reach their financial goals effectively.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-5-maintains-confidentiality-and-ethical-behavior">5. Maintains Confidentiality and Ethical Behavior</h2>



<p>Keeping financial information private and not revealing unauthorized data is essential to build a trustworthy reputation. As an accountant, it is your responsibility to keep sensitive data like salaries, bonuses, and taxes secure and confidential.</p>



<p>It is also important to practice good ethics and adhere to a set of moral principles while doing your job. This includes being honest, transparent, and fair in your dealings with colleagues and clients. Furthermore, prioritizing your clients’ best interests and avoiding conflicts will help you establish yourself as a reliable accountant in the market.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-6-punctual-and-organized">6. Punctual and Organized</h2>



<p>In today’s fast-paced business world, two essential skills to master are time management and planning organized schedules. Keeping track of events can help prioritize tasks based on importance and urgency. Setting realistic timelines for each task and adhering to deadlines are critical aspects of efficient time management.</p>



<p>Being able to break big tasks into smaller ones helps. Good accountants are highly passionate about their work and are eager to get the job done smoothly and on time. This can only be possible if you do not succumb to procrastination. Some planning and scheduling can save you time, boost productivity, and make this otherwise hectic profession less stressful.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-7-computer-literacy-and-effective-use-of-technology">7. Computer Literacy and Effective Use of Technology</h2>



<p>Having an affinity for math helps in becoming a good accountant. However, it doesn’t end there. Since your work will involve doing a lot of calculations, you need to know how to use the various software and tech tools.</p>



<p>From a client’s perspective, a tech-savvy person would be a preferable match because of their proficiency in creating and updating spreadsheets as well as their ability to pick up on the latest technology. Technology has revolutionized how we do business, reducing errors and improving accuracy. A good accountant must also have the proper software and know how to use it to their favour, so understanding the <a href="https://www3.technologyevaluation.com/selection-tools/p/features-list/c/bi">features and functions of BI software</a> as well as accountant-specific software is an absolute must.</p>



<p>There are numerous data analysis software that can help identify trends and give valuable insights into financial data, helping you make better-informed decisions. A study revealed that about <a href="https://contentsnare.com/accounting-statistics/">37. 58% of accountants said updating technology has improved efficiency and productivity</a></p>



<p>In addition to being proficient with technology, a good accountant must have organizational skills. Since the job requires maintaining a large amount of financial data, great record-keeping abilities are necessary to guarantee everything is in order. Attention to detail helps avoid making mistakes that can have serious effects on the client’s financial health.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Conclusion</h2>



<p>With an increasingly high number of individuals committing to entrepreneurship, good accountancy has become more important than ever before. With ever-changing tax laws and economic uncertainty looming across the world, sound financial advice has become pivotal to businesses&#8217; success. </p>



<p>Companies seek accountants with adequate financial intelligence so they can be guided into making informed decisions and keeping their businesses healthy, and if you want to be a successful accountant, you must possess the characteristics mentioned in this article.</p>



<p>An exceptional accountant will surely know how to build and maintain a healthy relationship with clients by understanding their challenges and focusing on providing them with tailored solutions that will help them scale their business. Lastly, being a good accountant is about making your mark in the business community as a trustworthy advisor and strategic partner.</p>
